8:
Ah, she just left. Said something
about meeting someone.
16:
Greetings, Esmeralda. I was
wondering if we could chat again
today.
19:
We're not even open yet...
Unfortunately, I'm too busy to
entertain you any further.
21: I see... In that case, I shall be quick.
24:
Esmeralda... Please leave my friends
alone.
27:
You've been observing Alk and Stella
through me, correct?
29:
I've met countless people like you,
all with that same cunning look in
their eyes.
31:
Heh... And here I thought you were
just a naïve little princess.
33:
So... What are you going to do to
convince me?
44:
We also noticed this woman's foul
intent. Let us help you, Princess Lilith!
55:
I have come here to talk, woman to
woman. I will not permit such
violence to interrupt us.
57:
Besides, if I cannot overcome such a
trifling band of brutes myself...
61:
I couldn't possibly stand as equals
alongside Estel and Adjudicus!
65:
Now then, Esmeralda... Shall we
continue?
68:
Hmph, seems like hiring security was
a waste of money.
69:
So what is it you're so desperate to
talk about? Surely this isn't simply
about your little friends.
71:
It is not. I would like to negotiate with
you.
74:
Esmeralda... The people of this land
once destroyed an entire mountain
to create a place they could call
home... Do you think you could do it
again?
77: You want us to make another island?
78:
Ha... Ahaha! Not only are you naïve,
you're a FOOL!
80:
Fine, I accept your ambitious
dreams with open arms.
83:
...Not the most lethal attack, but the
flash up close could certainly
incapacitate some...
86:
Yeah, an attack like that was more
than enough for weaklings like this.
A crafty one, ain't she?
91:
Shakari... Your daughter has grown
into a strong, reliable leader.
101:
Whoa, you were out late... Where did
you go?
115:
It's more emotional exhaustion than
anything else. It's been a long time
since I had to put on such a brave
front.
118:
But now I finally see a path forward.
It may be but a single path, but it's a
start...
121:
Stella, Alk... Would you like to
accompany me on an outing?
124: Huh? Now? But I thought you said—
133:
As long as you're not too tired from
today. But it's kinda late. Where
would we go?
137:
Well... I suppose there's only one
place to go...
143:
There, preparations are complete!
We can swim now!
150:
Jeez, where do you get all this
energy?
153:
...You know, you seem different from
when we first arrived.
157:
I'm sure I do. I've had plenty of
lessons from my teacher Stella now.
161: I have nothing left to teach you.
165:
I'll admit it—at first, it felt wrong for
me to be having fun when my
people are struggling...
169:
However, my opinion shifted
somewhere along the line. I would
like my people to see such breaks
as a necessity, not a luxury.
171:
To live is to do more than endure
and survive. I wish for all of us to
thrive...
175:
Does that include the beastfolk and
fiends too?
178:
Of course. Everyone deserves a life
free of excessive burden.
180:
I want to move forward without
overly fixating on my status and
what it means.
183:
That... sounds like one ambitious
dream.
187:
One I intend to see come true.
Instead of being ashamed of my
status, I should make use of it. Just
like this bikini.
193:
Well, such revealing attire allowed
me to better understand the
thoughts of men and society's view
of the female body.
199:
Therefore... It is all right for you to
relax, Alk.
206:
You don't need to work so hard to
avoid staring at my bosom.
216: ...I'll be more careful not to look...
220:
Hm? But I just said it was fine, didn't
I? I've come to understand this
world's views on modesty, so I am
no longer embarrassed by my attire.
228: You seem to be having fun, Lilith.
